      <sec id="Sec16">
        <title>Refining alignments</title>
        <p id="Par55">SALT outputs the alignments of the reads mapped to the SNP-enhanced reference. SALT considers identical penalties for primary alleles and alternative alleles.</p>
        <p id="Par56">However, some downstream analyses are based on linear genomes, which requires realigning all hits to the primary reference. We present a refinement program (Polish) to realign all hits to the linear reference genome and compute the optimal alignment using the standard Smith–Waterman algorithm. The realignment results are stored in SAM format.</p>
      </sec>
